"Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["From the vocabulary word denoting the plant (Old English <i>fearn</i>). Modern use of this word as a given name dates from the 19th century, when it is also recorded occasionally as a boy's name in the United States. In some instances the given name may be a transferred use of the surname derived in the medieval period from the vocabulary word."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Angharad ferch Dafydd was born about 1342, in Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom as the daughter of Dafydd ap Madog and Gwenllian ferch Hywel. She had at least 4 sons and 3 daughters with Maredudd ap Gwilym."},"et":{"about 1342–":"umbes 1342–Surnud","1342–Female":"1342–Surnud","1435–Male":"1435–Surnud","1338–Male":"1338–Surnud","1355–Male":"1355–Surnud","1364–Male":"1364–Surnud","1475–Male":"1475–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1317–Male":"1317–Surnud","1338":"1338","1435":"1435","Abt 1355":"umbes 1355","1355":"1355","1475":"1475","1364":"1364","1342":"1342","about 1475":"umbes 1475","about 1342":"umbes 1342","about 1364":"umbes 1364","1317":"1317","of Bacheirig, Llanfair Dyffryn, Denbighshire, Wales":"Llanfair Dyffryn Clwyd, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Madog Ll Siryf, Wales":"Wales","of,,Merionethshire,Wales":"Merionethshire, Wales, United Kingdom","of Caerdegog,Llanfechell,Anglesey,Wales":"Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom","Llanfairfechan,Uchaf,Caernarvonshire,Wales":"Llanfairfechan, Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1342–":"noin 1342–Kuollut","1342–Female":"1342–Kuollut","1435–Male":"1435–Kuollut","1338–Male":"1338–Kuollut","1355–Male":"1355–Kuollut","1364–Male":"1364–Kuollut","1475–Male":"1475–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1317–Male":"1317–Kuollut","1338":"1338","1435":"1435","Abt 1355":"noin 1355","1355":"1355","1475":"1475","1364":"1364","1342":"